651
01:29:56,000 --> 01:30:16,000
And when he said that to me, my whole life came full circle because all the things that I've been doing in my life was the same thing. I just never had a phrase or title or caption I could put on it. But he just lit me up when he made that one statement. I had to go and stand for those that won't stand and those that can't stand.

652
01:30:16,000 --> 01:30:43,000
That's the clutch of it. Let me know that his life was second, the past day. He said to me, he said, they can kill me, but they can never kill me. In other words, I would be greater in depth than I am in life for what I stand for. And I'll tell people, I said, you know, Dr. King lost his flesh, but his spirit and his meaning and his energy and his vision will live for eternity.

653
01:30:43,000 --> 01:31:12,000
How many people can say that when I leave here, they'll remember what I stood for. Say not a whole bunch of people that's going to get that life. And I go back and I'll tell you, I say, you know, when you sit back and you think about what he told me, it began to think about the fact that, you know, they got like John Wayne, Liz Taylor, Rock Hudson, all these luminaries that they had in the entertainment field, whether it's music, or whatever.

654
01:31:12,000 --> 01:31:41,000
But when they die, they're gone. But you sit back and you look at Paul Robinson, they talk about him every day, Rosa Parks, they talk about her every day, Harriet Tubman, every day, Gandhi, every day, Tommy Smith, every day, Peter Norman, every day. So it began to make you think.

655
01:31:41,000 --> 01:31:46,000
Nelson Mandela, every day, they'll be talking about him.

656
01:31:46,000 --> 01:32:00,000
Okay. Based on the fact that these individuals that I said, the movie star, they were man made icons and these other individuals are God giving icons. And that's the big difference.

657
01:32:00,000 --> 01:32:08,000
Why doesn't that they remember them, but they don't talk about John Wayne? Well, that's the thing you heard them talk about Liz Taylor.

658
01:32:08,000 --> 01:32:21,000
You understand? But I hear them talking about Rosa Parks all the time. And people have to start looking at these things and trying to have someone to stand and you're like, everybody got them voids in their life. Like I told you I experienced when I was a kid.

659
01:32:21,000 --> 01:32:33,000
The difference is I was trying to fill a voice. A lot of people are still running around in the corner. You don't understand the package. They can't put the package together in their head.

660
01:32:33,000 --> 01:32:41,000
That's why a lot of people don't stand for anything other than the dollar because they think the dollar is their God.

661
01:32:41,000 --> 01:32:50,000
